{"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tests allow developers to prove that the code they write is working as expected."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If code is not working correctly, bug trackers are often used to track the work"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"necessary to fix the underlying problem. It is often useful to associate"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specific bugs with tests that reproduce them or verify they are fixed."}]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Bugs” as described in this document may also be referred to as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“issues.” To avoid confusion with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Issue","isActive":true},{"text":" type in the testing library,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this document consistently refers to them as “bugs.”","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Associating-a-bug-with-a-test","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Associating a bug with a test"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To associate a bug with a test, use the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/bug(_:relationship:)-duvt","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/bug(_:relationship:)-40riy"},{"type":"text","text":" function. The first argument to this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function is the bug’s "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"identifier"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" in its bug-tracking system:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Test(\"Food truck engine works\", .bug(\"12345\"), .bug(67890))","func engineWorks() async {","  var foodTruck = FoodTruck()","  await foodTruck.engine.start()","  #expect(foodTruck.engine.isRunning)","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The bug identifier can be specified as an integer or as a string; if it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified as a string and matches certain formats, the testing library is able"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to infer additional information about it. For more information on the formats","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recognized by the testing library, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/BugIdentifiers","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Specifying the relationship between a bug and a test","anchor":"Specifying-the-relationship-between-a-bug-and-a-test","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the nature of the relationship between a bug and a test is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unspecified. All the testing library knows about such relationships is that they"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"exist.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to customize the relationship between a bug and a test. Doing so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allows the testing library to make certain assumptions, such as that a test is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expected to fail, or that a failure indicates a regression that requires"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"attention from a developer."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To specify how a bug is related to a test, use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"relationship","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameter of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/bug(_:relationship:)-duvt"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/bug(_:relationship:)-40riy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function. For example, to indicate that a test was written to verify a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"previously-fixed bug, one would specify ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".verifiesFix"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@Test(\"Food truck engine works\", .bug(\"12345\", relationship: .verifiesFix))","func engineWorks() async {","  var foodTruck = FoodTruck()","  await foodTruck.engine.start()","  #expect(foodTruck.engine.isRunning)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Kinds of relationship","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Kinds-of-relationship"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The testing library defines several kinds of common bug\/test relationship:"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Relationship","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use when…"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".uncoveredBug"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"… a test run failed, uncovering the bug in question."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".reproducesBug"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"… a bug was previously filed and the test was written to demonstrate it.","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":".verifiesFix","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"… a bug has been fixed and the test shows that it no longer reproduces."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".failingBecauseOfBug"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"… a test was previously passing, but now an unrelated bug is causing it to fail.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".unspecified"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"… no other case accurately describes the relationship.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Traits"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Testing"}],"title":"Associating bugs with tests","roleHeading":"API Collection","role":"collectionGroup"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/BugIdentifiers","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/bug(_:relationship:)-duvt","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/bug(_:relationship:)-40riy","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Bug"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/testing\/associatingbugs"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Associate bugs uncovered or verified by tests.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/EnablingAndDisabling","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AddingTags","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AddingComments","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/LimitingExecutionTime","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Parallelization"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AssociatingBugs","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://org.swift.testing/documentation/Testing/AddingTags":{"title"